cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL. 

The paper focuses on deep learning and deep reinforcement learning approaches for query-based multi-document summarisation, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses features based on similarity with the query, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of neural networks and reinforcement learning also suggests categories such as cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of deep learning architectures, which falls under the category of cs.DL (Deep Learning).
